# Project rules

## Core Principles

### 1. **CSS Variables and Design Tokens**

- **ALWAYS** use CSS variables from `src/index.css`
- For colors: Use `var(--ui-size-)`, `var(--icon-accent)`, `var(--text-primary)`, etc.
- For typography: Use `var(--text-xs)`, `var(--text-xm)`, `var(--text-base)`, `var(--font-medium)`, etc.
- For shadows: Use `var(--shadow-md)`
- To conditionally render styling use classnames package `import cn from 'classnames'`
- Do NOT add hover and focus styling!

### 2. **Semantic Markup & Accessibility (CRITICAL)**

- Use semantic HTML elements: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`
- Prefer `<article>` instead of `<main>` for component-level content wrappers in generated components.
- Proper heading hierarchy: h1 → h2 → h3
- ARIA labels for interactive elements: `aria-label`, `aria-describedby`, `role`
- Use `<button>` for actions, not `<div>` with onClick
- Form labels must be associated with inputs: `<label htmlFor="id">` + `<input id="id">`
- Images must have `alt` attributes
- Focus management for keyboard navigation
- Color contrast considerations (use design system colors)

### 3. **Navigation Links**

- Use `<a>` tags only for external links with `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`

### 4. **React Optimization & Memoization**

- Use `React.memo()` for component memoization
- Use `useCallback()` for event handlers passed as props
- Use `useMemo()` for expensive calculations and computed values
- Extract static data to custom hooks (e.g., `useData()`)
- Use `React.useCallback` for functions passed to child components

### 5. **Event Handlers & Callbacks**

- **ALWAYS** provide predefined callback stubs for interactive elements
- Button callbacks: `const handleClick = useCallback(() => { logger.info('Button clicked'); }, [])`
- Input callbacks: `const handleChange = useCallback((value: string) => { logger.debug({ value }, 'Input changed'); }, [])`
- Form submissions: `const handleSubmit = useCallback((e: React.FormEvent) => { e.preventDefault(); logger.info('Form submitted'); }, [])`

### 6. **List Data Management (CRITICAL)**

- **IF** design shows repeated elements with same layout but different data/styling colors/icons:
  - Extract data to a variable (e.g., `const items = [...]` or custom hook)
  - Use `.map()` to render list items
  - Provide proper `key` prop for each item
  - Example:

    ```tsx
    const items = [
      { id: 1, title: 'Item 1', description: 'Description 1' },
      { id: 2, title: 'Item 2', description: 'Description 2' }
    ];
    return (
      <ul>
        {items.map(item => (
          <li key={item.id}>
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p>{item.description}</p>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    );
    ```

### 7. **CSS Modules Styling**

- Use camelCase for CSS class names
- Responsive design with CSS Grid/Flexbox
- Use 2-space indentation
- Prefer CSS Grid for layout, Flexbox for alignment

### 8. **Component Structure Template**

#### Internal Component Structure Order (CRITICAL)

Внутри тела компонента код должен располагаться строго в следующем порядке:

1. **Library hooks** — хуки из библиотек (react-i18next, react-hook-form, etc.)
   ```tsx
   const { t } = useTranslation('componentName');
   const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm();
   ```

2. **Store hooks** — получение данных из стора (Zustand, Redux)
   ```tsx
   const { slides, currentSlide } = useSlideStore();
   const user = useUserStore(state => state.user);
   ```

3. **Custom hooks** — собственные хуки приложения
   ```tsx
   const { data, isLoading } = useGetLayouts();
   const { theme } = useTheme();
   ```

4. **Local variables** — простые вычисления без хуков
   ```tsx
   const isDisabled = !value || isLoading;
   const fullName = `${firstName} ${lastName}`;
   ```

5. **Refs** — создание рефов
   ```tsx
   const containerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
   const inputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);
   ```

6. **State** — локальное состояние компонента
   ```tsx
   const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
   const [value, setValue] = useState('');
   ```

7. **Derived data (useMemo)** — вычисляемые данные
   ```tsx
   const filteredItems = useMemo(() => items.filter(...), [items]);
   ```

8. **Callbacks (useCallback)** — обработчики событий
   ```tsx
   const handleClick = useCallback(() => {...}, []);
   ```

9. **Effects (useEffect)** — побочные эффекты
   ```tsx
   useEffect(() => {...}, [deps]);
   ```

10. **Early returns** — условные возвраты перед рендером
    ```tsx
    if (isLoading) return <Spinner />;
    if (error) return <ErrorMessage error={error} />;
    if (!data) return null;
    ```

11. **Render** — возврат JSX
    ```tsx
    return (<section>...</section>);
    ```

### 9. **Acceptable Third-Party Libraries**

- For complex UI: `react-virtualized`, `react-window` (for large lists)
- For animations: `framer-motion`, `react-spring`
- For forms: `react-hook-form` (lightweight)
- For date/time: `date-fns` (over moment.js)
- For tooltips: `react-tooltip`
- Keep dependencies minimal and justified

### 10. **Development Guidelines**

- Generate dummy/mock data for lists and dynamic content
- Export SVG icons from Figma and wrap in React components
- Ensure responsive design (mobile-first approach)
- Using enams for enumerables values and create type by this enuns
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Add proper error boundaries for complex components
- Test accessibility with screen readers in mind
- Always place import statements at the beginning of the file.

## Checklist Before Delivery

- [ ] All colors use CSS variables from `src/index.css`
- [ ] Typography uses design system variables
- [ ] Semantic HTML structure implemented (prefer `<article>` over `<main>`)
- [ ] ARIA labels and accessibility attributes added (translated)
- [ ] Event handlers implemented with `useCallback`
- [ ] Repeated elements extracted to data arrays and mapped
- [ ] Component wrapped with `React.memo`
- [ ] Component internal structure follows the defined order (library hooks → store → custom hooks → local variables → refs → state → memo → callbacks → effects → early returns → render)
- [ ] Responsive design implemented
- [ ] TypeScript interfaces defined for props
